  "market_context": "Gold (XAUUSD) had taken out multiple highs to the left with failure swings and a fair value gap. The daily candle formed a bearish reversal closure, suggesting price should now retrace lower toward an unfilled daily fair value gap below.",
  "key_observation": "After a bearish daily reversal closure, the hourly time frame confirmed with a change in state of delivery, and the 5-minute formed a V-shaped reversal plus continuation order block, aligning all three time frames bearish into a daily FVG target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily, observed that multiple highs to the left were swept with failure swings and a daily fair value gap left below, then a bearish reversal closure formed — establishing bearish daily bias.",
    "Step 2: Identified the daily fair value gap below as the draw on liquidity / target for the next day's price action.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the hourly time frame and confirmed a change in state of delivery: price swept the highs and closed back through the series of up-close candles, validating the bearish swing point.",
    "Step 4: Anticipated the wick high of the daily candle to form within the lower half of the previous day's range and looked for a candle 2 or candle 3 closure as a point of interest.",
    "Step 5: First reversal attempt produced only a doji-like closure; dropping to 5-minute showed price made equal highs and consolidated, so the setup was passed on (it then ran the high).",
    "Step 6: Waited for a V-shaped reversal on the hourly with aggressive displacement down, which formed a new continuation order block on the hourly structure time frame.",
    "Step 7: Identified a bearish candle 2 closure within a small hourly fair value gap retesting the continuation order block.",
    "Step 8: Dropped to the 5-minute and found a fair value gap point of interest plus a short-term low sweep; waited for the close below to confirm continuation order block.",
    "Step 9: Entered on the close / retest with stop on the protected high, targeting 2R and extending the runner toward previous day low and the daily fair value gap."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade triggered on the 5-minute retest; expansion occurred from candle 5 onward, delivering a clean drop into the daily fair value gap below — well beyond the 2R minimum target.",
  "lessons": "Align daily, hourly, and 5-minute bias before entering. Skip setups when the reversal is weak or too close to highs; wait for a V-shaped reversal and a continuation order block. Use lower-time-frame invalidation to target higher-time-frame objectives for greater R:R.",
